      p.pageTitle Flippy The Robot
      .clearfix
      hr
      #row1.contentRow
        .rowdesc
          p Flippy is a toy robot  physically built on the Arduino platform and programmed with the modern webstack for its control surface.
        .rowimg
          img(src="img/flippy_img1.jpg", height="100%", width="100%")
      .clearfix
      hr
      #row2.contentRow
        .rowdesc
          p Flippy was built as a project to introduce my son to electronics and robotics.
        .rowimg
          img(src="img/flippy_img2.jpg", height="100%", width="100%")
      .clearfix
      hr
      #row3.contentRow
        .rowdesc
          p Flippy's is physically based on the Arduino open source hardware platform.
        .rowimg
          img(src="img/flippy_img3.jpg", height="100%", width="100%")
      .clearfix
      hr
      #row4.contentRow
        .rowdesc
          p What's really cool is that Flippy's control surface is programmed using HTML, CSS & Javascript.
        .rowimg
          img(src="img/flippy_img4.jpg", height="100%", width="100%")
      .clearfix
      hr
      #row5.contentRow
        .rowdesc
          p Flippy receives instructions via Breakout.js. If you have a computer, a modern web browser and an active network connection, you can control Flippy.
        .rowimg
          img(src="img/flippy_img5.png", height="100%", width="100%")
      .clearfix
      hr
      #row6.contentRow
        .rowdesc
          p Here's a video of my son's reaction to Flippy on his birthday.
        .rowimg
          iframe(width="560", height="315", src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/OFdzrCj10w0", frameborder="0", allowfullscreen)
      .clearfix
      hr
      p If you'd like to learn more, hit me up on the twittters (#darronet)
